The analysis involves wavelet approximation, which is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the performance of compressed sensing in image reconstruction, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper provides new error bounds and theoretical justifications for the success of compressed sensing, which could be of interest to researchers in signal processing (cs.SI).
